<br>
Monks avoid damage better, but compared to a similarly-equipped warrior they'll still die faster because they have less hit points (and hence CHeals are even less effective). They can't taunt, and they don't get defensive disciplines. As a main tank on an uber mob, they really sucked even before the nerf... as a secondary tank for normal XP groups they were able to do a very decent job. Now, unless you're a twink with a fungi and other uber gear, they're not.<br>
<br>
As for warriors being the best tanks, the fact is, they aren't, except for uber mobs where their defensive discipline or larger hit point pool is vital. The tank's job is to get aggro and keep it, Paladins and SKs are usually better at that than a warrior, and Monks suck at it, getting aggro when they don't want it, and losing aggro when they do want it. Quite why Sony chose to nerf monks rather than upgrade warriors so they were the best tanks is beyond me.<br>
<br>
Seriously, this change is a good idea if it makes Warriors into better tanks; but it's the kind of thing they should have been doing months ago rather than nerfing other classes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=woonx>woonx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 353<br> <font color=#333333>(2/20/03 5:09:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8828.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Shield blocking</span><hr size=1> They nerfed mitigation on monks because a &quot;leather&quot; class was mitigating as well as a &quot;plate&quot; class. That was nonsense, that was fixed. Monks still tank pretty decent, just not as good as before. <br>
<br>
As for the &quot;no guild in their right mind would ever use a monk as main tank in that situation if they had the choice of a warrior or knight&quot;, that wasn't true before the nerf. ANY guild would have been MUCH better ALWAYS making the monk take rampage, and, like I said, any guild would have been much better using a monk as MT if it wasn't for ONE factor, higher HP on warrior. Let me explain.<br>
<br>
The reason why monks were not used as MT is simply this. The max round of a given mob (for example AoW) would almost kill a monk in 1 round. So while the monk took less damage overall than the warrior, there was always the chance to see the monk drop in 1 round due to the random number generator burping the best melee round possible for the mob. Now with rampage you can pretty much ignore that factor because the mob won't hit rampage target nearly as often as the MT. So for rampage, before monk mitigation nerf, a monk was by far the best way to deal with rampage since they took less damage (thus requiring less healing) than any other class. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=75721">Woon</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://tde.e-slackers.net/">&lt;TDE&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>
