Monk can only affect themselves, they have nothing MORE to add to the raid than their melee damage.  Even if some are pulling, the rest are in that situation.<br>
<br>
And in that situation IF you can only take say 20 people and 10 are monks, or 10 are rogues, you're going to take 10 rogues because monks are simply rogue-lites and would reduce you're  over all DPS with out giving anything else. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Infact at some levels post 60 a mage PET can totally and utterly replace and out perform an averagely equiped monk of the same level.<br>
Now that is pretty dire, not for pets they are FINE as they are.  But equally shows how subpar monk are at the momment.  Being replaced by a pet is NOT a good postion for a class to be in.<br>
<br>
Other non-pure melee classes (and make no mistake this IS a pure melee problem - warriors and even rogues suffer from this situation at various times) have similar issues.  Other classes with more UTILITY and variablity do not suffer it anything like as much.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>MONKS WERE OVERPOWERED.<br>
<br>
This wasn't a change to make them different. This was a change to take away something that was making them way too good. Monks were broken. They didn't need somethign to even them out, because they were already better than other classes in the first place. The same goes for our own rod nerf, mages were -TOO GOOD- while rods operated like that, we were mana factories capable of single handedly doubling the mana pools of the healers and nukers. Our rods were changed to be less good, because they were broken! You don't see me crying that mages need something to compensate for the rod nerf, do you?<br>
<br>
No sympathies from me buddy.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Again complete <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>ROT</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Were monks soloing 4 mobs at once in PoP?<br>
<br>
Were monks even going to be soloing in PoP?<br>
<br>
Were monks getting 2-3 aaxp's an hour (like dire charmer)?</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Monk were overpowered? Nope, I think not.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
A small percentage of monks tanked a bit to well in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>some</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> situations because of:<br>
<br>
1. Very, very good geat from sloppy itemisation.<br>
2. A broken game engine.<br>
<br>
SO instead of some mild changes and tweaks to change the problematic things VI decide to BREAK monks.<br>
<br>
And monks should be happy about this?<br>
(whilst MANY other classes are happily <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>SOLOING</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> more AAXP than a monk could get in a month with a group, assuming they can GET a group, which many cannot)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>This makes me laugh. Monks get two, count them, TWO straight melee damage increases past 60 (ignoring weapons), and then at 65 get a whole brand new 15/20 ratio weapon just for dinging. Monks are not hurting for damage, they get more FREE damage than anyone else in the game, without gear outdamaging every other melee class that isn't a rogue.<br>
<br>
Hell, i'd say rogues need a little help in this area. They are stuck using velius and kunark weapons for the most part, until they get into the highest end<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yes an small as they are it's not enough (not unless you can get your atk high enough - which UBER monks can (and also they can get thier AC high enough to mitigation the nerf as much as is possible) and average monks cannot.<br>
<br>
But really what you you want monk fist to be? 10/30?<br>
And remember to use those fists they have to forgot their epic haste <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>and</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> stats one those 2 weapons.<br>
<br>
Not to mention that by L65 15/20 is not all that great.<br>
<br>
Rogues ARE suffering from this at high levels admittedly - AND this as much as things like very high atk is what is helping uber monk DPS 'catch up'.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>And monks do fine in pop, both as tank and as puller. Funny that rogues can't say the same. Funny that you do just <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>a little less damage than rogues</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. Funny that this.. sort of makes sense.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
A take it 'a little less' is about 30-40% in your book then?<br>
I'd say that was a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>tad</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> more than a 'little' myself.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Quote:<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
And lets not forget that nerfing monks did NOT fix warriors (who now still find themselves behind pal &amp; sk's)<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
In what way? Warriors still mitigate better, warriors still have disc defensive and evasive. Warriors still have extremely high hp. The only problem is warriors cna't instnatly grab aggro, and they shouldn't be able too anyway.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
In the sense that there is very little if any reason to take a warrior over a SK or a Pal.<br>
Because that intial agro can mean the difference in PoP between a live and dead group member.<br>
Warriors are in a similar unwanted and subpar situation to monks.  Frankly SK's and Pal's would have been the tank of choice (over monks and warriors) even without the mitigation nerf.<br>
<br>
But nerfing monk did not help or fix warriors at all <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  (and warriors need help - which I hope they'll get with the shield changes form this very thread). <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>and make it possible for joe schmoe unguilded to survive?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
<br>
I think you're showing your elitest colours a bit there. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Except monks are still the highest damage class other than rogues. They can still tank well enough in any exp group. They can still tank any boss outside of pop. They can still pull perfectly fine. They are still getting into groups, and are needed in guilds.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Except they are not the 2nd highers DPS, more like 4th or 5th.<br>
They are 5th or 6th choice for most tanking duties.<br>
Outdoor pulling is in efficent with a monk compared to other classes.<br>
And monks are increasingly LFG (although this is not purely a monk or even pure melee problem, they just suffer the most). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2974<br> <font color=#333333>(2/22/03 7:13:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8828.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Shields, not monks</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>/shout TRAIN TO ZONE!  Women and rangers first!</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
